Subject: [patch 1/1] qeth: remove header_ops bug
Content-Disposition: inline; filename=qeth.patch
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
List-Archive: <https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/>
List-Post: <mailto:linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org>
To: cebolinha@vila.local, netdev@vger.kernel.org, linux-s390@vger.kernel.org
Cc: cascao@linux.vnet.ibm.com, magali@vila.local, linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org, franjinha@linux.vnet.ibm.com, chico.bento@trash.net
List-ID: <linux-s390.vger.kernel.org>

From: Mônica Sousa <monica.sousa@vila.local>

Remove qeth bug caused by commit:
[NET]: Move hardware header operations out of netdevice.

Signed-off-by: Mônica Sousa <monica.sousa@vila.local>
---
 drivers/s390/net/qeth_main.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

Index: linux-2.6-monica/drivers/s390/net/qeth_main.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6-monica.orig/drivers/s390/net/qeth_main.c
+++ linux-2.6-monica/drivers/s390/net/qeth_main.c
@@ -6643,7 +6643,8 @@ qeth_netdev_init(struct net_device *dev)
	dev->vlan_rx_kill_vid = qeth_vlan_rx_kill_vid;
	dev->vlan_rx_add_vid = qeth_vlan_rx_add_vid;
 #endif
-	dev->header_ops = &qeth_null_ops;
+	if (qeth_get_netdev_flags(card) & IFF_NOARP)
+		dev->header_ops = &qeth_null_ops;

 #ifdef CONFIG_QETH_IPV6
	/*IPv6 address autoconfiguration stuff*/

